Beaver Meadows Remote Sensing

Matthew Ross

12/26/2017

This script is an example script for analyzing Landsat 5, 7, and 8 data in a harmonized way. The data used here is downloaded from Google Earth Engine using JavaScript code. This code pulls down every image ever taken by landsat over all of the beaver meadows provided by Ellen Wohl (nearish Rocky Mountain National park)

Libraries

Data read and data manipulation heavy lifting

Some quick exploratory plots

Annual variability in NDMI (moisture index) and NDVI (greenness)

Spatially averaged across sites, which is probably a bad idea, this should be spatially averaged across known ecotypes (forest, prairie, open water)

load('harmonizedmeadows.RData')


#Spatial means 
sum.mead %>%
  group_by(name,year) %>%
  summarize(ndvi=median(ndvi),
            ndmi=median(ndmi)) %>%  gather(.,key=index,value=value,-name,-year) %>%
  ggplot(.,aes(x=year,y=value,color=index)) +
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_manual(values=c('blue2','green3')) +
  facet_wrap(~name) + 
  theme(legend.position=c(.5,.15))

Standard deviation across space year to tyear

#Spatial means 
sum.mead %>%
  group_by(name,year) %>%
  summarize(ndvi=sd(ndvi),
            ndmi=sd(ndmi)) %>%  gather(.,key=index,value=value,-name,-year) %>%
  ggplot(.,aes(x=year,y=value,color=index)) +
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_manual(values=c('blue2','green3')) +
  facet_wrap(~name) + 
  theme(legend.position=c(.5,.15))

Map of NDVI variance over time over each pixel (all sites)

#Spatial means 

sum.mead %>%
  group_by(lat,lon,name) %>%
  summarize(var.ndvi=var(ndvi)) %>%
  ggplot(.,aes(x=lon,y=lat,color=var.ndvi)) +
  geom_point(shape=15,size=2) + 
  facet_wrap(~name,scales='free') + 
  theme(legend.position=c(.8,.1))

Map of NDVI variance over time over each pixel (big sites)

#Spatial means 

sum.mead %>%
  filter(name %in% c('NSV BM','NSV other','Hollowell BM','Cow Cr BM','Big T BM','Beaver Cr BM')) %>%
  group_by(lat,lon,name) %>%
  summarize(var.ndvi=var(ndvi)) %>%
  ggplot(.,aes(x=lon,y=lat,color=var.ndvi)) +
  geom_point(shape=15,size=7) + 
  facet_wrap(~name,scales='free') + 
  theme(legend.position=c(.9,.1))
